<section class="diag-section" id="patterns">
  <div class="diag-inner">
    <div class="section-label" style="color: var(--accent-amber);">What We Usually Find</div>

    <div class="diag-intro">
      <h2>Most accounts aren't broken in obvious ways.</h2>
      <p>The campaigns are running. The reports look reasonable. But underneath, the same patterns show up again and again.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="diag-grid">

      <!-- Pattern 1: ACoS Security Blanket -->
      <div class="diag-card">
        <div class="diag-card-visual">
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">ACoS (Branded)</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value green">12%</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill green" style="width: 85%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">ACoS (Non-Brand)</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value red">Cut</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill red" style="width: 10%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">New Customer Acq.</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value red">Flat</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill red" style="width: 15%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">Revenue Growth</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value amber">Stalled</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill amber" style="width: 22%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-verdict">⚠ Metric healthy. Business standing still.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diag-card-content">
          <h3>ACoS looks fine. Growth doesn't.</h3>
          <p>Campaign-level ACoS is hitting its target, but it's being carried by branded search terms that would convert with or without ads. Meanwhile, targets that could actually drive new customers are getting cut because they don't hit the number. The metric everyone watches is healthy. The business is standing still.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pattern 2: Structure Without Strategy -->
      <div class="diag-card">
        <div class="diag-card-visual">
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">Active Campaigns</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value amber">47</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill amber" style="width: 90%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">Target Overlap</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value red">High</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill red" style="width: 75%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">Negation Coverage</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value red">12%</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill red" style="width: 12%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">Structural Intent</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value red">None</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill red" style="width: 5%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-verdict">⚠ Not a strategy. An accumulation.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diag-card-content">
          <h3>Ads everywhere. No structure anywhere.</h3>
          <p>Multiple campaigns, overlapping targets, converting search terms spread across several ad groups with no negation and no intent behind the organization. Nobody's managing the architecture. They're managing the metrics. The campaigns aren't a strategy. They're an accumulation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pattern 3: Fear of Change -->
      <div class="diag-card">
        <div class="diag-card-visual">
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">Legacy Campaigns</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value amber">Active</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill amber" style="width: 80%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">Ad Spend Trend</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value red">↑ Rising</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill red" style="width: 70%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">Total Revenue</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value amber">→ Flat</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill amber" style="width: 40%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-meter">
            <div class="diag-meter-label">
              <span class="diag-meter-name">Campaigns Paused</span>
              <span class="diag-meter-value red">0</span>
            </div>
            <div class="diag-meter-bar">
              <div class="diag-meter-fill red" style="width: 0%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-verdict">⚠ Spend rising. Revenue flat. Nothing changed.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diag-card-content">
          <h3>Nobody wants to turn anything off.</h3>
          <p>After one or two agencies, the account is layers on top of layers. Every campaign is "generating sales," so nothing gets paused or restructured, even when ad spend keeps climbing and total revenue isn't keeping pace. The seller knows something is off but can't justify changing what appears to be working.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <p class="diag-closer">The common thread: <strong>the numbers everyone focuses on are fine. The business outcomes those numbers are supposed to drive aren't.</strong> That's usually where we start.</p>
  </div>
</section>

